{
  "texts": [
    "The embedded patches are aggregated with the positional embeddings generated through E pos, a trainable positional embedding tensor.",
    "The resultant z 0 is fed into the transformer encoders; the encoders learn the global features from the embedded patches of the mass through multi-headed selfattention layers.",
    "The encoders generate a sequence of tokens.",
    "Those tokens are fed into the MLP to generate the prediction of the class label if it is a benign mass or a malignant mass.",
    "Transfer learningThis work adopted the transfer learning concept due to the lack of publicly available mammograms and to minimize the training time."
  ]
}